# Tooling (agents)

**What:** Pointer index for repo tooling — `.cursor/tools/`, **`skills/`** (canonical skill bodies), **`.cursor/skills/ray-test/`** (entry router), `aspire.svc/.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/mcp.json`. Opens linked `SKILL.md`/rule end-to-end; does not duplicate stack guidance.

**When:** Add/change tools, skills, or MCP; run repo CLIs (e.g. aspire registry). Not product UI or `*.svc/` domain code.

**How:** Index → follow linked `SKILL.md`/rule end-to-end. No invented paths or install commands. Link `constants.mdc`, `solution.mdc`, `infra.mdc` — do not re-declare values.

## Index

| Task | Path |
|------|------|
| **Skills hub (start here)** | **`.cursor/skills/ray-test/SKILL.md`** → **`skills/catalog.md`** |
| Project constants init (**prj**) | **`skills/prj/SKILL.md`** → `.cursor/rules/constants/constants.mdc` |
| Terraform CLI + **tf** skill | **`skills/tf/SKILL.md`** → `.cursor/tools/tf-tool/card.md` |
| tf-tool rule pointer | `.cursor/rules/tools/terraform-tool.mdc`, `.cursor/tools/tf-tool/` |
| AWS deploy CLI (**jp-tool**) | `.cursor/tools/jp-tool/`, `.cursor/tools/jp-tool/card.md` |
| Aspire registry CLI | `.cursor/tools/aspire/` |
| Aspire registry (guided) | `aspire.svc/.cursor/skills/aspire-registry-tool/` |
| Cursor rules | **`skills/rules-create/SKILL.md`**, `.cursor/rules/rules/rules.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/rules/template.mdc` |
| DynamoDB IaC | **`skills/aws_dynamodb_create/`** |
| S3 IaC | **`skills/aws_s3_create/`** |
| Skill catalog (human) | **`skills/README.md`** |
| Python tools | **`.cursor/rules/python/python.mdc`** — script requests → uv app in **`.cursor/tools/<name>/`**; no one-off `.py` files |
| AWS / IaC | `.cursor/rules/infra.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/iac/terrafrom.mdc` |

## Rules

1. **Skills first** — use **`.cursor/skills/ray-test/SKILL.md`** when the user has not named a skill; then **`skills/<id>/SKILL.md`**. Existing skill wins over improvised commands or layout.
2. **Script → uv app** — never create one-off `.py` files; a “script” request is a new uv project per **`.cursor/rules/python/python.mdc`** (`.cursor/tools/<kebab-name>/` + `pyproject.toml`, `src/`, tests, README).
3. **One tool, one home** — each uv tool lives in exactly one folder under **`.cursor/tools/<name>/`**; do not add orphan scripts beside it.
4. **MCP** — only `.cursor/mcp.json`; merge into `mcpServers`; user reloads MCP after edits.
5. **Scope** — tooling invocation/maintenance only; product/UI/domain → `solution.mdc` (`frontend/`, `aspire.svc/`, `*.svc/`).
